What is Ubuntu?
  Ubuntu is one of many Linus distros.  This version is popular due to ists ease of use and windows like feel.

Why would you choose to install the LTS version over regular Ubuntu releases?
  The LTS or Long Term Support version just as the name implies has more support and is more widely used so there is mor information readily available online.

What is the Ubuntu GNOME Shell?
  This is similar to other Shell applications such as POWERSHELL from Windows and can utility scripts to preform serveral tasks.

How do I install software from the command line?
  Utilizing the SUDO command you would basically walk the computer through where a file is and what to do with it.
